Want those shoulders to grow? Check your ego and go lighter:

So last few days I've been off my game, luckily I feel great today so I smashed out a big shoulder session. This is just a highlight. 
I start with the shoulder engaged rather than relaxed then go through the rep but go down half way and back up again. 
With this you have to cut the weight down so you can really focus on the deltoids rather than using traps and momentum to force the rep. This will mean that the shoulders are forced to work harder therefore better for growth. 
I keep my thumbs pointed up so that the shoulder joint is in a healthy position. And I work on holding a external rotation whilst moving which is great for longevity in the joint. 
The gloves I use are @theactivehandsco
